itemDescription: British-born architect who worked extensively in Australia in the early twentieth century

wikipedia_page.main: Samuel Charles Brittingham (1860 - 12 November 1944) was a British-born architect who worked extensively in Australia in the early twentieth century.

response: * November 12 – Samuel Charles Brittingham, Australian architect (born 1860)

The Central Telephone Exchange, Melbourne is a building in Central Melbourne, Australia, constructed between May 1907 and early 1909 by the Reinforced Concrete & Monier Pipe Construction Co. headed by engineer Sir John Monash, and designed by architect Samuel Charles Brittingham. The building includes an early example of a reinforced concrete saw-tooth roof.Holgate, A.
